The paper discusses the development of an application and API for monitoring real-time edit activity on Wikipedia and Wikidata. This involves analyzing edits to answer questions such as "Bots vs. Wikipedians, who edits more?" and "Which is the most anonymously edited Wikipedia?". This work involves data mining, natural language processing, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
